  "issue_number": 506,
  "issue_title": "[bug] quick router does not parse spoken-number temperature setpoints (only digits)",
  "issue_body": "### Summary\n\nThe quick router parses spoken-number durations (since #490) but not spoken-number temperature setpoints, so \"set the oven to four hundred degrees\" does not route while \"set the oven to 400 degrees\" does.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n`parse_temperature_target` in `crates/genie-core/src/tools/quick.rs` extracts the value by finding a token that contains an ASCII digit and calling `parse::<f64>()`:\n\n```rust\nlet value_token = value_text\n    .split_whitespace()\n    .find(|token| token.chars().any(|ch| ch.is_ascii_digit()))?;\nlet value = value_token\n    .trim_matches(|ch: char| !ch.is_ascii_digit() && ch != '.')\n    .parse::<f64>()\n    .ok()?;\n```\n\nA spoken amount (\"four hundred\", \"seventy two\") has no digit token, so `find` returns `None` and the utterance does not route to `home_control` `set_temperature`. Meanwhile `set_timer` already handles spoken numbers via `parse_spoken_number` (#490).\n\nMeasured with the deterministic quick router (no LLM, no HA):\n\n```\ngenie-ctl bfcl-predict-quick --cases cases.jsonl --out preds.jsonl\ngenie-ctl bfcl-score --cases cases.jsonl --predictions preds.jsonl --json\n```\n\nwith cases:\n\n```\n{\"id\":\"oven-digit\",\"prompt\":\"Set the oven to 400 degrees\",\"expected_tool_calls\":[{\"tool\":\"home_control\",\"arguments\":{\"entity\":\"oven\",\"action\":\"set_temperature\",\"value\":400}}]}\n{\"id\":\"oven-spoken\",\"prompt\":\"Set the oven to four hundred degrees\",\"expected_tool_calls\":[{\"tool\":\"home_control\",\"arguments\":{\"entity\":\"oven\",\"action\":\"set_temperature\",\"value\":400}}]}\n{\"id\":\"thermostat-spoken-compound\",\"prompt\":\"Set the thermostat to seventy two degrees\",\"expected_tool_calls\":[{\"tool\":\"home_control\",\"arguments\":{\"entity\":\"thermostat\",\"action\":\"set_temperature\",\"value\":72}}]}\n{\"id\":\"thermostat-spoken-connector\",\"prompt\":\"Set the thermostat to one hundred and five degrees\",\"expected_tool_calls\":[{\"tool\":\"home_control\",\"arguments\":{\"entity\":\"thermostat\",\"action\":\"set_temperature\",\"value\":105}}]}\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nSpoken-number temperatures route to `home_control` `set_temperature` with the parsed value, the same way spoken-number durations route to `set_timer`. `tool_name_accuracy` / `argument_accuracy` = 1.0 for the four cases above.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nOnly the digit case routes; the three spoken cases produce no tool call:\n\n```\nparse_accuracy: 0.25, tool_name_accuracy: 0.25, argument_accuracy: 0.25\n```\n\n### Hardware\n\nNon-Jetson (x86_64 dev / cross-build host)\n\n### GenieClaw version / commit\n\n`main` @ `1e01954` (v1.0.0-rc.1 workspace)\n\n### Additional context\n\nThe cardinal parser (`parse_spoken_number` / `cardinal_word`) currently lives inside `quick.rs` and is only used for durations. Sharing it for setpoint values fixes the gap. PR to follow.",
